						<summary>

						<p>Registers a gift of gold towards feeding a Brāhmaṇa well versed in the Vēdas on the occasion of the midday service, by Puśaṁkaṉ Pirānterumāṉ son of Dēvaṉār of Taḷikkoṭṭūr in Neṉmali-nāḍu. The record is dated in the <hi rend="bold">2nd year of Parakēsarivarman</hi> probably Parāntaka I.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. IV. No. 520.</p>						

						</summary>
